scenario_text: Increase the vehicle capacity to 100 to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when serving high-demand customers more efficiently.
Decrease the number of available vehicles from 2 to 1 to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when serving all customers with limited resources.
Decrease the vehicle capacity from 50 to 30 to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when serving customers with higher demand relative to reduced vehicle capacity.
Decrease the vehicle capacity from 50 to 20 to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when serving customers with demands that exceed the reduced capacity.
Scenario: 'Increase the demand of all customers by 50% to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when the demand significantly exceeds the current vehicle capacity.'
Decrease the vehicle capacity from 50 to 10 to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when serving customers with demands that greatly exceed the significantly reduced capacity.

Decrease the vehicle capacity from 50 to 15 to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when serving customers with demands that are likely to exceed the reduced capacity, potentially leading to infeasibility.

Decrease the vehicle capacity from 50 to 25 to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when serving customers with demands that may exceed the reduced capacity, potentially leading to infeasibility.
Decrease the vehicle capacity from 50 to 5 to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when serving customers with high demands that will likely exceed the drastically reduced capacity.
Decrease the number of available vehicles from 2 to 0 to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when attempting to serve customers without any delivery resources.
